PWR8601.Description: The power buttons for all multinode sleds in the chassis are disabled. The operation to disable the power button is only applicable to the multinode sleds available, and does not affect other servers in the chassis.
PWR8601.Resolution: To enable the chassis power button use the CMC RACADM command line interface (CLI) or CMC Web interface. At the CLI, enter "racadm config -g cfgChassisPower -o cfgChassisSledPowerButtonEnable 1". Using the Web interface, click Server Overview > Power > Control. Clear the Disable power button for all multinode sleds in the chassis" check box.
PWR8601.Message: The multinode sled power button is disabled.

FAN0015.Message: %1 RPM is greater than the upper critical threshold.
FAN0015.Resolution: Remove and re-install the cooling device. If the issue persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
FAN0015.Description: The cooling device is not performing optimally. The cooling device may be installed improperly.

SUP0520.Message: Unable to update the %1 firmware to version %2.
SUP0520.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the problem persists, download the latest Update Package from your service provider and retry the operation.
SUP0520.Description: The firmware update operation for the component did not complete due to an internal error.

RFL2007.Message: Internal Dual SD Module %1 is writable.

RED011.Description: Current USC version does not support this component. Check InstanceID.
RED011.Resolution: Use the latest version of USC available if possible.

RAC993.Description: The job ID specified in the message was deleted.

RAC1112.Description: Unable to clear the pending state from the attributes for a RAID object. A job is currently running and iDRAC internal storage is in use.
RAC1112.Resolution: Retry the operation after any currently running jobs have completed. Jobs can be monitored by running the racadm command "racadm jobqueue view".
RAC1112.Message: Unable to delete the pending values for the specified device because the iDRAC internal storage is in use by a currently running job.

RAC0225.Description: Sending the test mail failed. This will prevent alert messages from being sent to this email address.
RAC0225.Resolution: Confirm that:1. A valid SMTP server address is configured in the iDRAC. 2. The remote email server is configured properly to send and receive emails.

CBL8501.Message: SAS cable %1 is connected to the incorrect expander.
CBL8501.Resolution: Reconnect the SAS cable to the correct expander and retry the operation.
CBL8501.Description: The SAS cable identified in the message is not connected to the correct expander.

RAC1021.Description: NIC objects are not available if NIC devices are not installed in the system, or if some iDRAC services are busy.
RAC1021.Resolution: Make sure the NIC devices are correctly installed in the system and retry the operation after the Collect System Inventory On Restart (CSIOR) feature has updated the system inventory. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
RAC1021.Message: NIC objects are not available in the current system configuration.

RAC1004.Description: The smart card login cannot be enabled, because the Active Directory Single Sign On is enabled.
RAC1004.Resolution: Disable Active Directory Single Sign On (SSO) using "racadm set iDRAC.ActiveDirectory.SSOEnable <0 | Disabled>", and retry the operation.
RAC1004.Message: The smart card login cannot be enabled.

RAC938.Message: Successfully initiated configuration XML file export operation invoked by the %1.
RAC938.Description: The configuration XML file export operation was successfully initiated after it was invoked by the user specified in the message.

NIC508.Message: NIC teaming info is not currently available.

SWU8513.Message: Successfully updated the IOM infrastructure firmware of slot %1.
SWU8513.Description: The firmware update operation of IOM infrastructure is successful.

VDR36.Description: Virtual disk initialization is in-progress. This alert is provided for informational purposes.

DH001.Resolution: Try again. If the error persists, use RACADM command racreset to clear the issue.
DH001.Message: Resource needed to perform the operation is unavailable.

SWC8609.Message: Server Profiles: unknown response received from server: %1 for operation [%2] because of one or more of the following reasons: 1) iDRAC is not ready. 2) Lifecycle Controller of the server is disabled.
SWC8609.Resolution: Make sure that iDRAC on the server identified in the message is operating and that Lifecycle Controller is enabled, and then retry the operation. If the issue persists, perform a virtual reseat of the server and retry the operation. To perform a virtual reseat of the server, on CMC Web interface, select Chassis Overview -> Troubleshooting -> Reset Components. On the Reset Components page, select Virtual Reseat from the drop-down menu for the server identified in the message.
SWC8609.Description: The CMC was unable to perform the operation described in the message because of one or more of the following reasons: 1) iDRAC is not ready. 2) Lifecycle Controller of the server is disabled.

RAC0235.Description: When uploading an image to the vFlash partition, the operation is unresponsive, and has timed out.
RAC0235.Resolution: Try uploading the vFlash image again.

SWC0051.Description: Unable to retrieve license information due to an iDRAC communication error.
SWC0051.Resolution: Exit Lifecycle Controller and retry the operation. If the problem persists, do the following: 1) Turn off the system and disconnect the power cord. 2) Wait for five seconds. 3) Reconnect the power cord, turn on the system, and retry the operation.
SWC0051.Message: Unable to retrieve iDRAC license information.

RAC0104.Description: An invalid PIN was entered. Too many log in attempts with a Smart Card login can result in a user being locked out of the system.
RAC0104.Resolution: 1. Enter a valid Smart Card PIN and try again.2. Use a different Smart Card.

SYS037.Description: Operation validation is unsuccessful. The command, target and operation data are all validated before an update is performed. If any of them are missing or incorrect the operation does not complete successfully.
SYS037.Resolution: Enable the Collect System Inventory on Restart attribute using Lifecycle Controller and restart the system. Retry the operation after the system restarts.

SUP0511.Description: The Diagnostic application (Embedded Preboot System Assessment - Enterprise UEFI Diagnostics) is not installed or is corrupt.
SUP0511.Resolution: Update the Diagnostics application using the Firmware Update feature in Lifecycle Controller. For the latest Update Packages, contact your service provider.

SUP030.Description: The value of the ProxySupport parameter must be TRUE if the Proxy IP and User Credentials need to be provided for the operation requested.
SUP030.Resolution: Do not specify Proxy IP and User Credential parameters if the ProxySupport parameter is FALSE.
SUP030.Message: Proxy IP and User Credential pare valid only if the ProxySupport parameter is TRUE.

SWC0303.Description: The syntax of the fwupdate command is invalid.
SWC0303.Resolution: Refer the help text for fwupdate subcommand.
SWC0303.Message: The -r option is not valid with any other option.

UEFI0080.Message: PCIe link speed is not optimal for %1. Expected link speed: Gen %2 and actual link speed: Gen %2.
UEFI0080.Resolution: Do one of the following: 1) Turn off the input power to the system and turn on again. 2) Update the PCIe device firmware. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
UEFI0080.Description: The PCIe link speed is not optimal for the identified PCIe device.

LC063.Description: All jobs must be completed before creating a new job.
LC063.Resolution: Retry after all the existing jobs are completed or deleted.
LC063.Message: Cannot create new jobs until the existing running jobs are completed or deleted.

RED042.Message: A recurring operation of type %1 was not created because the necessary user access rights are not available.
RED042.Resolution: Use a username that has the necessary access rights and retry the operation.
RED042.Description: The necessary user access rights for performing the operation identified in the message are not available for the username used to access the iDRAC.

UEFI0024.Description: The Management Engine firmware is not responding to the BIOS via the HECI interface.
UEFI0024.Resolution: Remove input power from the system, wait for 30 seconds, and re-apply input power. Turn on the system.
UEFI0024.Message: The Management Engine is not responding.

SYS046.Description: An error occurred while copying the Server Configuration Profile from the network share.
SYS046.Resolution: If the file is being copied from an NFS share, make sure that it is accessible from iDRAC. If the file is being copied from a CIFS share, make sure that it is accessible from iDRAC using the share credentials provided. Test the network share access using the Test Network Connection method. For more information, see the Lifecycle Controller User's Guide.
SYS046.Message: Unable to import the Server Configuration Profile from the network share.

SEL1504.Description: There is not enough available power for two CMC's to operate.
SEL1504.Resolution: Check overall power consumption and power status.
SEL1504.Message: The chassis management controller (CMC) is not redundant. Insufficient resources to maintain normal operations.

RAC0605.Description: There are no jobs to be displayed.
RAC0605.Message: There are no jobs to be displayed.

AMP0304.Message: The system board %1 current is outside of range.
AMP0304.Resolution: Review system power policy, check system logs for power related failures, and review system configuration changes.
AMP0304.Description: Product documentation contains information on correct configuration. The failure could also be caused by a faulty component or related cabling. System performance may be degraded.

JCP017.Description: The current job count has reached the maximum value supported. No more jobs are created until the number of jobs on the system is reduced. Completed jobs are automatically deleted if they are older than the DeleteOnCompletionTimeout setting.
JCP017.Resolution: Do one of the following to reduce the job count: 1) Delete one or more jobs and retry the operation. 2) Wait until existing jobs have an elapsed time since completion that is greater than the delete on completion timeout setting and are automatically deleted. 3) change the DeleteOnCompletionTimeout setting using the WSMAN API to a smaller value so that completed jobs are automatically deleted sooner.
JCP017.Message: Job creation request unsuccessful. Maximum number of jobs reached.

SYS044.Description: Unable to collect the configuration information for one or more components. An internal error occurred while processing component information.
SYS044.Resolution: Enable Collect System Inventory On Restart (CSIOR) using Lifecycle Controller and restart the system. Make sure that inventory collection is complete before retrying the operation. For more information, see the Lifecycle Controller User's Guide.
SYS044.Message: Unable to export one or more component configurations.

RAC003.Resolution: Refer to the profile document and provide the required parameters.
RAC003.Description: One or more required parameters for the method are missing.

PWR8687.Message: The Chassis Management Controller (CMC) is unable to turn on the storage sled controller installed on server in slot %1 because the server does not have a Mezzanine card.
PWR8687.Resolution: Install a Mezzanine card in the Mezzanine card slot of the server identified in the message, and then retry the operation.
PWR8687.Description: The Chassis Management Controller (CMC) is unable to turn on the storage sled controller installed on the server in the slot identified in the message because the server does not have a Mezzanine card. A Mezzanine card position is identified with the following numbers: For quarter-width server, the position number is 1. For half-width server mezzanine C & B maps to position numbers 1 & 2 respectively. For full-width server, Mezzanine C & B on the upper- or left part of the server maps to position numbers 1 & 2 respectively. Mezzanine C & B on the lower- or right part of the server maps to position numbers 3 & 4 respectively.

PSU8515.Description: Unable to set the Enable Dynamic Power Supply Engagement attribute.
PSU8515.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Retry the operation. 2) If the issue persists, review the tracelog for more details. To retrieve the tracelog, in the CMC Web interface, go to Troubleshooting > Diagnostics page and enter the "gettracelog" command, or use RACADM "gettracelog" command. If the issue continues to persist, contact your service provider and provide the tracelog.
PSU8515.Message: Unable to set the Enable Dynamic Power Supply Engagement attribute.

BIOS029.Description: The BIOS password cannot be configured because an Export Server Profile operation is already running.
BIOS029.Resolution: Wait until the current export operation is completed, and then retry the operation.
BIOS029.Message: Unable to change the BIOS password because an Export Server Profile operation is already running.

RAC937.Message: Successfully initiated configuration XML file import operation that was invoked by the %1.
RAC937.Description: The configuration XML file import operation was successfully initiated after it was invoked by the user specified in the message.

SUP0528.Description: An internal error occurred in the Lifecycle Controller while generating the firmware comparison report.
SUP0528.Resolution: Exit the Platform Update wizard and retry the operation. If the problem persists, update the Lifecycle Controller firmware to the latest version and retry the operation.
SUP0528.Message: Unable to generate a firmware comparison table.

UEFI0221.Message: An error occurred during DDR memory channel initialization on memory slots: %1.
UEFI0221.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Remove input power to the system, 2) Reseat the DIMM module and 3) Restart the system. If the issue persists, then replace the faulty memory module(s) identified in the message.
UEFI0221.Description: An error occurred during DDR memory initialization during the Read Voltage Training phase.

UEFI0176.Message: Multiple Quad Rank DIMM modules are installed on a DDR channel. Refer to DIMM modules on memory slots: %1.
UEFI0176.Resolution: Only a single Quad Rank DIMM module can be installed on a channel. Populate memory modules in a supported configuration. For more information, see the platform Owner's Manual.
UEFI0176.Description: A memory population violation has been detected on the identified DIMM slots.

PWR8584.Message: Chassis Management Controller is unable to turn on server-%1 because the power supply redundancy is lost and Performance Over Power Redundancy feature is disabled and the power required is less than the available power.
PWR8584.Resolution: To enable the server to be turned-on, on the Power Configuration page in the Web UI, enable the server Performance Over Power Redundancy option . Using the RACADM utility, run the following command "racadm config -g cfgChassisPower -o cfgChassisPerformanceOverRedundancy 1". Then retry the operation.
PWR8584.Description: If power redundancy is lost and the server Performance Over Power Redundancy feature is disabled, the server turn-on will not be allowed.

HWC5034.Message: A link tuning failure detected on IO module %1.
HWC5034.Resolution: Update the CMC firmware. If the problem persists, contact support.
HWC5034.Description: Link tuning table not supported for this IO modular.

PCI3014.Message: A non-fatal PCIe error detected on a component at slot %1.
PCI3014.Resolution: Cycle input power, update component drivers, remove and re-install the device at the next scheduled service time.

ISM0021.Description: The OS Collector application did not start successfully on the server operating system (OS) because the OS Collector executable was not found.
ISM0021.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Retry the operation. 2) If the issue persists, reinstall the OS Collector on the iDRAC to the most recent version available, and then retry the operation.
ISM0021.Message: The OS Collector application did not start successfully on the server operating system (OS) because the OS Collector executable was not found.

RDU8518.Message: CMC%1: active CMC%1 requests Standby CMC to go active state.
RDU8518.Description: The active CMC requests the Standby CMC to go active. If the user did not initiate this request, review the chassis log for the reason.

CTL71.Message: Attempted to import an incompatible Physical Disk on %1.
CTL71.Description: This alert is provided for informational purposes.

BIOS015.Message: AttributeValue cannot be changed to read only AttributeName %1.
BIOS015.Description: A set attribute operation was attempted on a read only attribute.

SYS082.Description: The request to preview the Server Configuration Profile import operation completed. Some changes specified in the configuration profile will not be successfully applied in an import configuration profile operation.
SYS082.Resolution: Identify the configuration changes that cannot be completed successfully by 1) Export the Lifecycle Log review the configuration results in the entries for the preview job or 2) Retrieve the preview operation configuration results using the GetConfigResults() method. Retry those changes that did not complete in a separate import operation.
SYS082.Message: Completed the preview of Server Configuration Profile import operation. Some changes specified in the configuration profile will not be successfully applied in an import operation.

UEFI0084.Description: One or more PCI Parity errors (PERR) have occurred.
UEFI0084.Resolution: Check the System Event Log (SEL) to identify the PCI device that caused the PERR. Update the identified device firmware. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
UEFI0084.Message: One or more PCI Parity errors (PERR) have occurred.

UEFI0043.Description: Unable to enable the TXT feature because the processor does not support TXT.
UEFI0043.Resolution: Install a TXT-capable processor and retry the operation.
UEFI0043.Message: Unable to enable the TXT feature because the processor does not support TXT.

DIS006.Description: Auto Discovery operation was successful in establishing connection and getting certificate. Auto Discovery feature is no longer needed and has been disabled.
DIS006.Message: Auto Discovery operation successful. Disabling Auto Discovery feature.

FCD8504.Description: The card was installed and activated on another chassis. To use this card, it must be deactivated (uninstalled) on the other chassis.
FCD8504.Resolution: Remove the card and install it on the chassis where the feature is activated.
FCD8504.Message: The feature was previously activated on another chassis.

LC038.Description: Lifecycle Controller is locked by another instance of the Hardware Inventory export process. Allow the process to complete before attempting another export operation.
LC038.Resolution: Do one of the following: 1) Rerun the command after about 2 minutes 2) Reset the iDRAC and rerun the command.
LC038.Message: An instance of Hardware Inventory export is already in progress.

DIS009.Message: Notification of iDRAC IP address changed to %1 sent to Provisioning Server.
DIS009.Description: iDRAC IP address sent to Provisioning Server.

HWC4013.Resolution: Check presence, re-install or reconnect, then re-attempt the update. If the problem persists, contact support.
HWC4013.Message: Hardware unsuccessfully updated for embedded NIC.

PWR2210.Message: The system was forced into a soft-off state.

UEFI0214.Message: An error occurred during DDR memory channel initialization on memory slots: %1.
UEFI0214.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Remove input power to the system, 2) Reseat the DIMM module and 3) Restart the system. If the issue persists, then replace the faulty memory module(s) identified in the message.
UEFI0214.Description: An error occurred during DDR memory initialization during the Basic Receive Enable Training phase.

PDR63.Message: A bad disk block on %1 cannot be reassigned during a write operation.
PDR63.Description: A write operation cannot complete because the disk contains bad disk blocks that could not be reassigned. Data loss may have occurred. Data redundancy may be lost.

ASR0009.Description: The system is communicating to the baseboard management controller (BMC).
ASR0009.Message: The system returned from a watchdog timer event.

VF024.Description: The partition is locked by another operation.
VF024.Resolution: Wait for the partition to be unlocked and check the partition status to see if it is attached.

RAC972.Description: Configuration XML import and export operations require the specified username to have administrator role privileges.
RAC972.Resolution: Run the same command with a username that has an administrator role privileges.
RAC972.Message: Insufficient privileges to run the configuration XML file import or export operations.

UEFI0126.Description: The primary SD card is in write-protected mode.
UEFI0126.Resolution: No response action is required if this is intentional.
UEFI0126.Message: The primary SD card is in write-protected mode.

CTL1.Description: This event is retrieved from the controller when iDRAC storage monitoring was not running. Such events which are generated in the past are logged as informational severity.

ENC10.Description: You have changed the enclosure asset name. This alert is provided for informational purposes.

HWC6002.Message: The %1 controller is stuck in boot mode.
HWC6002.Resolution: Remove and reapply input power. If problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
HWC6002.Description: Information and status from the controller is unavailable.

BAR025.Description: For each component with firmware, an update is in progress.

RAC051.Resolution: Remove the unsupported parameter and retry the operation.
RAC051.Description: The parameter name is not supported.

PDR54.Message: A disk media error on %1 was corrected during recovery.
PDR54.Description: This message is generated after a disk media error is corrected on a physical disk.

LOG005.Description: The operation did not complete successfully because of an unknown error in iDRAC.
LOG005.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the issue persists, reset the iDRAC.
LOG005.Message: Cannot perform the operation due to an unknown error in iDRAC.

PSU0801.Resolution: Acquire the power supply firmware image and update the power supply indicated in the message.
PSU0801.Description: The Power Supply had a CRC error detected.

SWC0255.Description: Unable to open the specified file.

NIC005.Description: The number of AttributeName and AttributeValue parameters do not match.
NIC005.Resolution: Pass the same number of parameters for AttributeName and AttributeValue. Refer to documentation for method input parameter details.
NIC005.Message: Mismatch in AttributeName and AttributeValue count

MEM1212.Description: The memory may not be seated correctly, misconfigured, or has failed.
MEM1212.Resolution: Review system logs for memory exceptions. Re-install memory at location <location>.

HWC0009.Description: The vFlash SD card is missing or not inserted correctly. iDRAC is not able to enable vFlash SD card.
HWC0009.Resolution: Reinsert the vFlash SD card and retry the operation. If the problem persists:1) Turn off the system and disconnect the power cord.2) Wait for five seconds.3) Reconnect the power cord, turn on the system, and retry the operation.
HWC0009.Message: Unable to enable vFlash SD card.

RAC919.Description: Racadm could not export the inlet temperature history file to the specified remote share. This is because the specified share may be write- protected.
RAC919.Resolution: To export the file, change the permissions on the remote share. Else, create another share with write permissions.
RAC919.Message: Copy to remote share unsuccessful. Remote share might be write protected.

RAC0292.Description: This error is displayed when LDAP or Active Directory cannot find its certificate.
RAC0292.Message: A valid certificate is not loaded.

JCP026.Description: Update packages are being downloaded for other jobs initiated on this system. This job resumes when the downloads complete.
JCP026.Message: Update packages are being downloaded. This job resumes when the downloads are completed.

SWC0205.Message: Upload an SSL key to the RAC

RSI0001.Description: The Lifecycle Controller Remote Services instrumentation is available.
RSI0001.Message: The Lifecycle Controller Remote Services is available.

SWC0012.Description: The operation to retrieve the front panel security settings encountered an unexpected error while communicating with iDRAC.
SWC0012.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the problem persists:1) Turn off the system and disconnect the power cord.2) Wait for five seconds.3) Reconnect the power cord, turn on the system, and retry the operation.
SWC0012.Message: Unable to retrieve the front panel security settings.

RAC069.Description: Unable to complete the operation because the string length is less than the minimum supported length.
RAC069.Resolution: Enter a string value that is greater than the minimum supported length and retry the operation.
RAC069.Message: Unable to complete the operation because the string length is less than the minimum supported length.

CPU0704.Resolution: 1) Check system and operating system logs for exceptions. If no exceptions are found continue. 2) Turn system off and remove input power for one minute. Re-apply input power and turn system on. 3) Make sure the processor is seated correctly. 4) If the issue still persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
CPU0704.Description: System event log and OS logs may indicate that the exception is external to the processor.

RAC0762.Description: Unable to perform a firmware update because a valid catalog file is not available on the network share.
RAC0762.Resolution: Make sure that a valid catalog file is available on the network share and retry the operation.
RAC0762.Message: Unable to perform a firmware update because a valid catalog file is not available on the network share.

MEM1202.Message: Memory RAID redundancy is degraded. Check memory device at location(s) %1.
MEM1202.Resolution: Re-install the memory component. If the problem continues, contact support.

PDR79.Message: A user terminated Copyback from %1 to %1.
PDR79.Description: A user aborted an ongoing copyback operation. The operation did not complete.

BAR085.Description: The validation of the system profile backup file has failed. The retrieval of system information to validate the backup file has failed.
BAR085.Resolution: Restart the remote access controller, and retry the operation. If the error continues, use the remote access controller firmware to try the operation again.
BAR085.Message: Unable to collect System Information for Import Backup file validation.

BAR001.Description: A system profile export operation has been requested.

SWC1913.Description: Network Time Protocol configuration is enabled.
SWC1913.Message: Network Time Protocol configuration is enabled.

PDR1.Resolution: Wait for rebuild to finish, then copyback should resume.
PDR1.Description: This message is generated after a copyback stops on a physical disk during a rebuild operation.

RAC1179.Description: Unable to complete requested operation because a Type A/A USB cable is connected to the front panel USB port and the iDRAC is emulating a NIC device.
RAC1179.Resolution: To change the USB Management Port mode setting, remove the Type A/A USB cable from the front panel USB port and change the port mode settings.
RAC1179.Message: Unable to complete requested operation because an Type A/A USB cable is connected to the front panel USB port and the iDRAC is emulating a NIC device.

LC074.Description: The Certificate export operation did not complete successfully.
LC074.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the issue persists, restart the iDRAC and retry the operation.
LC074.Message: The Certificate export operation did not complete successfully.

PSU8510.Message: PSU in slot %1 FW updated successfully to version %2
PSU8510.Description: The firmware for the PSU identified in the message is successfully updated to the version displayed in the message.

PSU0001.Resolution: Remove and re-install the power supply. If the issue persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.

JCP020.Description: Existing jobs cannot be scheduled while an Export Server Profile or Import Server Profile job is running.
JCP020.Resolution: Retry the job scheduling operation after the export or import operation is completed.
JCP020.Message: Cannot schedule jobs while export or import operations are running.

PSU8503.Message: The PSU in slot %1 detected 220 VAC input voltage and does not match chassis configuration.
PSU8503.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Check if the input voltage of all the PSUs are the same. 2) If the input voltage of the PSU specified in the message is not the same, then remove the unmatched PSU.
PSU8503.Description: The input voltage of the PSU specified in the message does not match the input voltage of the PSUs already present in the chassis.

RED014.Description: A job for this update already exists in the queue and prevents the new job from being scheduled.
RED014.Resolution: Delete the existing job before scheduling a new update job. For Remote Services API consumers, enumerate all the jobs to find and identify the duplicate job. Then invoke the DeleteJob() method to delete this job and enable the new update job to be scheduled.
RED014.Message: Job for this device is already present.

RED034.Description: A firmware update operation is currently in progress.
RED034.Resolution: Check the firmware update job status. Wait for the current job to complete.

SWC8508.Message: Unable to capture Profile from server in slot %1
SWC8508.Resolution: Check if iDRAC is ready and system is running properly. Utilize the RACADM command by running "racadm getversion" to list all the servers and make sure the iDRAC version is displayed. If the iDRAC is listed as Not Ready then wait until it becomes ready. A Virtual Reseat may be required.

RDU8522.Description: The standby CMC identified in the message became the active CMC.

SWC0056.Description: Unable to export the file to the USB drive because it does not have the specified folder, does not have enough free space, or is read-only.
SWC0056.Resolution: Make sure that the USB drive contains the folder specified, has enough free space, or is not read-only. If the problem persists, reboot the system and retry the operation.
SWC0056.Message: Unable to export the file to the USB drive.

RAC1120.Description: The command could not be successfully run, because an incorrect Proxy type value was entered for the -pt option.
RAC1120.Resolution: Make sure that you entered either "http" or "https" as the proxy type. Enter the correct type, and then retry the operation.
RAC1120.Message: Unable to run the command, because an incorrect Proxy type is entered.

RAC0768.Description: iDRAC firmware is recently updated and iDRAC is still in the process of initializing. It is recommended to wait a few minutes before logging in so that the iDRAC initialization process can fully complete.
RAC0768.Resolution: Wait a few minutes to log in to iDRAC. Some iDRAC features may not be available for use if log in is continued at this time.
RAC0768.Message: iDRAC is currently initializing. Try logging in to iDRAC after few minutes because iDRAC is initializing after a recent firmware update process.

LC077.Description: The new certificate will not be in-use until iDRAC has been restarted.
LC077.Message: Certificate imported successfully. Reset iDRAC to apply new certificate. Until iDRAC is reset old certificate will be active

SWC0266.Description: The SD card may not be inserted/inserted properly.
SWC0266.Resolution: Ensure that the SD card is inserted in the server.
SWC0266.Message: Unable to perform the requested operation. Make sure SD card is inserted.

LC020.Description: The contents of the PKCS12 parameter was not valid because: 1) not a valid PKCS12 file 2) not a valid pfx file 3) did not contain a certificate that matched the private key in the file.
LC020.Resolution: Validate that the PKCS12 content was Base64 encoded. OpenSSL can be used to create or validate a PKCS12 encoding.
LC020.Message: PKCS12 decrypt of the certificate could not complete.

PDR113.Message: The %1 has reached or exceeded its warranted wear-out limit.
PDR113.Resolution: Back up the data on the device, and contact your service provider for further instructions.
PDR113.Description: The PCIe solid state device identified in the message has either reached or exceeded the warranted wear-out limit.

PSU8518.Message: Unable to access the PSU %1 FRU data.
PSU8518.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the condition persists, contact your service provider.
PSU8518.Description: The operation to read the FRU data from the PSU identified in the message did not complete successfully due to internal communication errors.

RAC0252.Description: The vFlash partitions are detached Therefore, the current operation cannot proceed.
RAC0252.Resolution: Attach the partitions and try again.
RAC0252.Message: One or more partitions are currently detached.

UEFI0103.Message: One or more memory initialization errors have occurred on memory slot: %1.
UEFI0103.Resolution: Replace the faulty memory module identified in the message.
UEFI0103.Description: One or more memory initialization error have occurred on the memory slot identified in the message.

SWC0158.Message: User CA certificate successfully uploaded to the RAC.

UEFI0253.Description: Unable to enable NUMA Fault Resilient Memory (FRM) feature due to the current configuration does not support it.
UEFI0253.Resolution: Check the DIMM population and hardware configuration to make sure NUMA FRM feature can be supported. For more information, see platform Owner's Manual.
UEFI0253.Message: Unable to enable NUMA Fault Resilient Memory (FRM) feature due to the current configuration does not support it.

STOR077.Description: A Patrol Read State change operation cannot be performed if the Patrol Read Mode is not set to Manual.
STOR077.Resolution: Change the Patrol Read Mode to Manual before performing a Patrol Read State change operation.
STOR077.Message: Unable to change Patrol Read State since Patrol Read Mode is not set to Manual.

FC016.Message: Unable to change the attribute value of the disabled attribute %1.
FC016.Description: A set attribute operation was not successful because the attribute is disabled.

SYS232.Message: Unable to transfer a file, %1, because of an unsupported destination file path value.
SYS232.Resolution: Make sure that the correct destination file path value is used, and then retry the operation.
SYS232.Description: The file cannot be transferred because of an unsupported destination file path value.

SWU8543.Description: The firmware update operation of CMC was not successful. The Image file was not accessible.
SWU8543.Resolution: Make sure that the CMC firmware image file is available at the location specified in the operation, and then retry the operation.
SWU8543.Message: Unable to update the Active CMC firmware. The Image file was not accessible.

RAC0743.Description: Unable to perform storage configuration operations because no storage controllers are detected on the server.
RAC0743.Message: Unable to perform storage configuration operations because no storage controllers are detected on the server.

CMC8518.Message: A double-height server is detected in the slot %1. However, the iDRAC in the server of bottom slot %1 is also responding.
CMC8518.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Remove the server in the bottom slot <slot number>. 2) Restart the Chassis Management Controller (CMC) and wait for the CMC to complete the startup process. 3) Reinsert the server identified in the message. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
CMC8518.Description: A double-height server is detected in the slot identified in the message. However, the iDRAC in the server of slot identified in the message is also responding. If a double-height server is already present in the chassis, the server in the bottom slot must not respond.

UEFI0047.Description: One or more keys in the keyboard is stuck and not functional.
UEFI0047.Resolution: Make sure that the key is not stuck in the keyboard and retry the operation.
UEFI0047.Message: One or more keys in the keyboard is stuck and not functional.

STOR0111.Description: The specified reference key is invalid.
STOR0111.Resolution: Verify that the correct reference key is specified. See the help text or documentation for valid reference keys.

BAR087.Description: The system profile import of Lifecycle Controller firmware images has failed.
BAR087.Resolution: Apply the Dell Update Package for this system. If the error continues, use the field service repair software to repair the Lifecycle Controller. Download all Dell Update Packages for USC, Diagnostics Driver Packs, and device firmware for all host system devices, install all packages and retry the operation.
BAR087.Message: Unable to Restore the Lifecycle Controller Firmware images.

SWC0076.Message: The following iDRAC internal storage partitions present in the system were not mounted during the system startup: %1.
SWC0076.Resolution: No response action required. If the issue occurs consistently during system startup, restart the iDRAC and then restart the system. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
SWC0076.Description: Lifecycle Controller detected that the iDRAC internal storage partitions identified in the message were not made available by BIOS during the boot process.

VFL0021.Description: The requested operation cannot be performed if one of the vFlash SD cards is in an 'attached' state.
VFL0021.Resolution: Detach the vFlash SD Card partitions by running the racadm command "racadm set iDRAC.vflashpartition.<partition number>.attachstate 0". and retry the operation.
VFL0021.Message: One of the vFlash SD Card partitions is already attached to the host operating system.

SEL1208.Message: A platform event filter action was executed.

RAC0649.Description: Unable to process the request, because data is not entered or not selected in one or more mandatory fields.
RAC0649.Resolution: Make sure to enter or select data in all the mandatory fields, and then retry the operation.

DIS012.Description: Factory signed client certificate is being used. Auto Discovery client is using this certificate for the SSL connection with the Provisioning Server.
DIS012.Message: Auto Discovery client using factory signed client certificate.

RRDU0005.Description: The current operating configuration cannot maintain redundancy. The unit may operate in a degraded state.
RRDU0005.Resolution: Review product documentation and SD card configuration.
RRDU0005.Message: Internal Dual SD Module is not redundant. Insufficient resources to maintain normal operations.

STOR030.Description: The requested operation cannot be completed because the specified controller is not found.
STOR030.Resolution: Provide a valid controller FQDD (Fully Qualified Device Descriptor) and retry the operation.

CTL104.Message: The Enhanced Auto Import Foreign Config value of %1 is set to %2.
CTL104.Description: The Enhanced Auto Import Foreign Config status of the controller identified in the message is set to the value identified in the message.

SYS258.Message: Unable to transfer a file, %1, because there is a problem with the remote host server's security certificate.
SYS258.Resolution: Make sure that the following are correct and retry the operation: a) the file transfer parameters b) the uploaded certificate corresponds to the remote host server c) the certificate subject name, CN part, matches the domain name used.
SYS258.Description: The remote host server certificate was validated against the uploaded certificate and the validation did not succeed. The remote host server certificate does not correspond to the uploaded verification certificate. The certificate subject name, CN part, may not match the domain name used. If the uploaded certificate is correct, the IP address of the remote host server may be incorrect, the certificate may be expired or this error could indicate a Man-In-The-Middle attack in progress.

HWC1201.Message: The sled %1 is removed from slot %2.
HWC1201.Description: The sled identified in the message is removed from the slot identified in the message.

OSD062.Description: The process of installing an operating system or hypervisor is started and is in progress.
OSD062.Message: The process of installing an operating system or hypervisor is started and is in progress.

RAC0631.Description: The requested network file share cannot be accessed, because an invalid network file share name is entered.
RAC0631.Resolution: Enter a valid network file share name, and then retry the operation.
RAC0631.Message: Unable to access the network file share, because an invalid network file share name is entered.

CTL94.Message: %1 has been successfully changed to operate in single controller mode.
CTL94.Description: The controller identified in the message has been changed to operate as a single controller and not as part of a fault tolerant pair.

PSU0045.Message: Power supply %1 status information successfully obtained.

VDR5.Description: The controller removed a virtual disk. This is due to a delete virtual disk operation, a reset configuration operation, or the removal of every physical disk that was a member of the virtual disk.

SYS050.Description: The Server Configuration Profile for the import configuration operation is not compliant with schema nesting checks. Only RAID controllers can have nested Component nodes up to a maximum nesting depth of three.
SYS050.Resolution: Make sure that the Server Configuration Profile is compliant with the system configuration schema published on delltechcenter.com/lc in the LC profile Schema Guide. Only RAID controllers can have nested Component nodes.
SYS050.Message: The Server Configuration Profile for import configuration is not compliant with schema nesting checks.

RAC0116.Description: The entered IPv6 address does not conform to the addressing standard or the supported IPv6 address range.
RAC0116.Resolution: Enter a valid Destination IPv6 Address.

SWC0309.Description: The platform does not support the specified functionality of fwupdate.
SWC0309.Message: The -p option is not supported with the interface being used.

SWU8515.Message: Unable to update the IOM firmware. Update Initiation was not successful. ErrorCode=0x%1.
SWU8515.Description: The IOM firmware update operation was not successful. Unable to initiate the Update process.

MEM0002.Message: Parity memory errors detected on a memory device at location %1.
MEM0002.Resolution: Re-install the memory component. If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
MEM0002.Description: The memory is operational. This is an early indicator of a possible future uncorrectable error.

VLT0104.Message: Processor module %1 voltage is outside of range.
VLT0104.Resolution: 1) Review system logs for power supply exceptions.2) Remove the processor module. Inspect processor socket for bent pins. 3) If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
VLT0104.Description: System hardware detected an over voltage or under voltage condition.If multiple voltage exceptions occur consecutively the system may power down in failsafe mode.

USR0177.Description: Configuring the Front Panel USB Port Mode to Automatic because the iDRAC is unable to retrieve the Front Panel USB Port Mode.
USR0177.Message: Configuring the Front Panel USB Port Mode to Automatic because the iDRAC is unable to retrieve the Front Panel USB Port Mode.

RAC0117.Description: The SD card is not present, or communication with the SD card is lost. This could result in reduced functionality and capabilities.
RAC0117.Resolution: This error may occur because: 1. Make sure the SD card is seated correctly. 2. The SD card is invalid. Insert a valid SD card of size greater than 256MB and try again.

SWC0131.Description: The destination Ip address must be configured for the Trap.
SWC0131.Resolution: Set cfgIpmiPetAlertDestIpAddr in cfgIpmiPet group using config subcommand for the corresponding index.
SWC0131.Message: Trap destination address must be configured.

UEFI0061.Description: The request to change one or more attribute(s) is being processed.
UEFI0061.Message: The request to change attributes is being processed.

RAC1150.Description: The export operation did not be complete successfully.
RAC1150.Resolution: Retry the export operation after five minutes.
RAC1150.Message: Unable to complete the export operation.

SYS247.Message: Unable to transfer a file, %1, because credentials are not entered, or the credentials entered do not correspond to an authorized user of the remote host.
SYS247.Resolution: Make sure that the correct credentials are entered, and then retry the operation.
SYS247.Description: The file cannot be transferred because credentials are not entered, or the credentials entered do not correspond to an authorized user of the remote host.

SWC1909.Message: User ID %1 RAC Privilege has been changed.
SWC1909.Description: The privilege level of the iDRAC User ID indicated in the message has been changed.

PCI1319.Message: A high-severity issue is detected in the SSD bay %1, Slot %2.
PCI1319.Resolution: Remove and reinsert the component identified in the message, and then monitor the log for a re-occurrence of the issue. If the issue persists, and occurs during server startup, update the component firmware. If the issue persists and occurs during OS runtime, restart the server and update the OS drivers for the component identified in the message.
PCI1319.Description: A high-severity issue was detected in the SSD bay identified in the message.

PWR8594.Message: Chassis Management Controller is unable to set the Enhanced Cooling Mode because the requested power %1 AC Watt is more than available power %2 AC Watt.
PWR8594.Resolution: Make sure there is enough power supply to enable the Enhanced Cooling Mode feature. Go to, the Chassis Overview > Power > Power Budget Status. In the Total Input Power Available For Allocation field view the available power. To add more power, insert more PSUs or remove unused components from the chassis.
PWR8594.Description: The available power is not sufficient to enable the Enhanced Cooling Mode feature.

VLT0210.Message: The memory module %1 %2 voltage is outside of range.
VLT0210.Resolution: 1) Review system logs for power supply exceptions.2) Reseat the memory module.3) If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
VLT0210.Description: System hardware detected an over voltage or under voltage condition.If multiple voltage exceptions occur consecutively the system may power down in failsafe mode.

HWC2011.Description: The riser blade cable may be necessary for proper operation. System functionality may be degraded.
HWC2011.Resolution: Check presence, then re-install or reconnect.
HWC2011.Message: The riser board cable or interconnect is not connected, or is improperly connected.

CMC8555.Description: An internal memory error occurred affecting the configuration database and CMC has initiated a failover . If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
CMC8555.Message: An internal memory error has occurred and a failover condition is detected.

PR25.Description: The system's configuration database is missing or is unreadable. This may be due to a user action such as Lifecycle Controller Wipe or a replaced motherboard.
PR25.Resolution: Enable the Collect System Inventory on Restart attribute of the Lifecycle Controller and restart the system. Alternatively, use the Unified Server Configurator utility.

BOOT002.Description: Unable to allocate required memory to perform the operation.
BOOT002.Resolution: Power cycle system and reapply firmware packages for Lifecycle Controller and iDRAC.

RAC0640.Description: The job could not be successfully scheduled, because an invalid value is entered for 'hour' while scheduling a job.
RAC0640.Resolution: Enter a correct value from 0 to 23, and then retry the operation.
RAC0640.Message: Unable to schedule, because an invalid 'hour' value is entered.

BIOS026.Description: The status of the Password cannot be set to locked, because currently there is a System Password change is pending.
BIOS026.Resolution: Wait until the pending System Password change is applied or delete the pending System Password change and retry the operation.
BIOS026.Message: Password status cannot be set to locked when a System Password change is pending.

JCP018.Description: A new job cannot be created until the existing Export job is completed or the job is deleted. There can only be one Export Server Profile job running at a time.
JCP018.Resolution: Do one of the following: 1) Retry the operation after the Export Server Profile job is completed. 2) Delete the scheduled Export job and retry the operation.
JCP018.Message: Cannot create new jobs until the existing Export job is completed or the job is cancelled.

MEM9016.Message: Correctable memory error rate exceeded for Dual In-line Memory Module (DIMM)%1.
MEM9016.Resolution: Re-install the memory component identified in the message. If the issue persists, contact your service provider. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
MEM9016.Description: The memory device identified in the message may not be operational. This an early indicator of a possible future uncorrectable error.

PWR8576.Message: Unable to turn on the Sleeve or Sled %1 after a virtual reseat operation.
PWR8576.Resolution: Retry the virtual reseat operation on the Sleeve or Sled identified in the message. If the issue persists, manually remove and reinsert the Sleeve or Sled in the chassis.
PWR8576.Description: The virtual reseat initiated on the Sleeve or Sled identified in the message successfully turned off the component. However, the Sleeve or Sled did not turn on successfully. A virtual reseat is the same as removing and inserting a Sleeve or Sled.

RAC033.Description: The specified attribute cannot be enabled since it depends on IPv4 to be enabled.
RAC033.Resolution: Enable IPv4 and retry the operation.
RAC033.Message: Unable to enable attribute because IPv4 is Disabled.

SWC0239.Description: The requested object is auto-assigned if IPv6 AutoConfig is enabled, and hence cannot be configured.
SWC0239.Resolution: Disable IPv6 AutoConfig and re-try the command.
SWC0239.Message: The requested object is not allowed to be configured if IPv6 AutoConfig is enabled.

VLT0233.Message: The mezzanine card %1 %2 voltage is greater than the upper critical threshold.
VLT0233.Resolution: 1) Review system logs for power supply exceptions.2) Reseat the mezzanine card.3) If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
VLT0233.Description: System hardware detected an over voltage or under voltage condition.If multiple voltage exceptions occur consecutively the system may power down in failsafe mode.

FAN1002.Description: The enclosure detected that a fan has failed and the enclosure is no longer functioning in optimal condition.

PWR8573.Message: The Chassis Management Controller is unable to communicate to the iDRAC, when trying to turn off the server %1.
PWR8573.Resolution: Wait for three minutes, and then retry the operation. If the issue persists, remove and reinsert the server and wait for the iDRAC to finish restarting before retying the operation.
PWR8573.Description: The Chassis Management Controller is not able to communicate with the iDRAC on the server identified in the message. Therefore the server could not be turned off. This situation may occur when iDRAC is restarting.

POW001.Description: Host failed to power up because chassis cover is open. This messages has been replaced by Message ID PWR2251.
POW001.Message: Power on permission error, chassis cover open.

SWC0252.Description: Invalid number of arguments were passed to the command.
SWC0252.Resolution: Refer the help text for the command, and enter the required parameters.
SWC0252.Message: No options were specified. The subcommand requires options to be used.

VDR19.Resolution: Recreate the virtual disk and restore data from a backup copy.
VDR19.Description: The reconfiguration operation was not completed. This may be due to a user action or a physical disk failure.

RAC1024.Description: The pending value is applied during the next reboot of system.
RAC1024.Resolution: Verify the job status using "racadm jobqueue view -i JID_xxxxx" command.

NIC501.Description: Autoconfig assigns values to the network components.
NIC501.Resolution: Disable Autoconfig and then modify the value.
NIC501.Message: The requested object is not allowed to be configured if Auto Config is enabled.

SEL1519.Message: The performance of CPU%1 that was automatically readjusted by Chassis Controller is functioning normally.
SEL1519.Description: The performance of CPU identified in the message, which was automatically readjusted by Chassis Controller, is functioning normally.

PSU1000.Message: Power supply cable has been removed from %1.
PSU1000.Resolution: Reconnect the power cable to the power supply unit if it was disconnected. Restore the input AC power supply. Make sure the power supply is restored to the enclosure from the mains.
PSU1000.Description: The power supply unit is not receiving input AC power. The power cable may not be connected properly or removed. This can happen if there is an AC failure or problems with the power strip attached to the enclosure power supply.

PST0009.Description: System BIOS has started PCI bus enumeration and video initialization.

MEM0020.Message: Memory device at location %1 is enabled.

JCP013.Resolution: Refer to the documentation for the operation being attempted and provide valid values for the identified parameters.
JCP013.Description: One or more required input parameters needed for the operation are missing.

SUP0108.Description: The firmware update is in progress and another update cannot be done.
SUP0108.Resolution: Wait for the update operation to conclude and then re-try.
SUP0108.Message: A firmware update operation is already in progress.

BAT1013.Message: Recharge count has exceeded the maximum limit for battery on %1.
BAT1013.Description: The battery cannot be recharged further.

SYS011.Description: A configuration job is scheduled to apply pending set attribute operations. Set operations are not allowed if there is an existing configuration job for a component.
SYS011.Resolution: Wait for the scheduled job to complete or delete the configuration jobs before attempting more set attribute operations.
SYS011.Message: Pending configuration values are already committed, unable to perform another set operation.

CTL65.Message: Attempted to import Unsupported Virtual Disk type RAID%1 on %2.
CTL65.Description: This alert is provided for informational purposes.

SWC8533.Description: The delete all keys for service accounts for all slots operation did not complete successfully due to problems encountered while saving the key file.
SWC8533.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
SWC8533.Message: Unable to complete delete all keys operation for service accounts for all slots due to problem saving key file.

SYS241.Message: Unable to transfer a file, %1, because of an unsupported proxy type value, %2.
SYS241.Resolution: Make sure that the correct proxy type value is entered, and then retry the operation.
SYS241.Description: The file cannot be transferred because of an unsupported proxy type value.

SWC1912.Message: User ID %1 User Access Right has been changed.
SWC1912.Description: User ID Access Right has been changed.

LC066.Description: The Export Certificate operation is already running and may take a few minutes to complete.
LC066.Resolution: Wait until the current operation is complete and then retry the operation.
LC066.Message: The Export Certificate operation is currently running.

USR8501.Message: Successfully closed Session process: pid=%1 sid=%2
USR8501.Description: The operation to close a user session using the process ID identified in the message was successful.

SWC0290.Message: Failed to configure object. Group: %1, Object : %2
SWC0290.Description: Failed to configure the object specified in the error message.

UEFI0178.Message: One or more memory correctable training errors have occurred on memory slot: %1.
UEFI0178.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Remove input power to the system, 2) Reseat the DIMM module and 3) Restart the system. If the correctable error persists, then replace the faulty memory module identified in the message.
UEFI0178.Description: One or more memory correctable training errors have occurred on the memory slot identified in the message. A corrected Read DQ/DQS error was detected.

RAC991.Description: The "jobqueue" command cannot be run, because the existing update jobs are transitioning to one of these states: "New", "Downloading", or "Running".
RAC991.Resolution: Wait until the existing update jobs are completed before retrying the operation. To monitor the status of the existing jobs, use the "racadm jobqueue view" command.

LIC501.Description: The attempted action requires a valid license for certain advanced features installed in the system but the required license is missing or expired.
LIC501.Resolution: Obtain an appropriate license then try again. If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to your product documentation to choose the contact method that is convenient for you.
LIC501.Message: A required license is missing or expired.

RAC0128.Description: A non-specific error has been detected while accessing the vFlash.
RAC0128.Resolution: Try the operation again in a few minutes. If the problem persists, reset iDRAC before trying the operation again.
RAC0128.Message: An error has occurred in vFlash.

PWR8521.Description: The chassis reset operation was completed.

VDR24.Description: The re-configuration operation on the virtual disk completed.

PWR8675.Description: AC power supply is detected in the NEBS configuration.
PWR8675.Message: AC power supply is detected in the NEBS configuration.

SWC0284.Description: Local Configuration using RACADM may be disabled.
SWC0284.Resolution: Check if the Local Configuration using RACADM is disabled and enable it through GUI.
SWC0284.Message: Failed to set the object value. Possible reason may be that Local Configuration using RACADM is disabled.

RAC0262.Description: This error message is displayed to indicate that the Preferred IPv6 DNS Server address does not conform to the required format.
RAC0262.Resolution: Enter a valid Preferred IPv6 DNS server address.
RAC0262.Message: The Preferred IPv6 DNS Server Address is invalid.

LC002.Description: A general failure occurred while executing the command.
LC002.Resolution: Verify network connectivity. If failure persists, reset the iDRAC to resolve the issue.

STOR010.Description: The operation cannot be completed either because the RAID level entered is not supported by the controller, or the current RAIDType of "MD Software RAID" does not allow the operation.
STOR010.Resolution: Enter a valid RAID level and retry the operation.
STOR010.Message: Unable to complete the operation either because the RAID level entered is not supported by the controller, or the current RAIDType of "MD Software RAID" does not allow the operation.

SYS178.Description: Unable to retrieve TTY log data because no storage controllers are detected in the server.
SYS178.Resolution: Make sure that at least one storage controller is present in the server, and then retry the operation.
SYS178.Message: Unable to retrieve TTY log data because no storage controllers are detected in the server.

SWU8553.Description: The firmware update operation of Active CMC was not successful. The firmware Image file could not be accessed.
SWU8553.Resolution: Make sure that the CMC firmware Image file is available at the location specified in the operation, and then retry the operation.
SWU8553.Message: Unable to update the Active CMC firmware. The Image file was not accessible.

BAR017.Description: A system profile backup file validation has been requested.

RSI0003.Description: The Remote Service database is being updated.
RSI0003.Message: The remote service is reloading data

SYS051.Description: Sometimes, the operating system on the server may not allow a graceful shutdown or may not complete within the specified graceful shutdown timeout. This error indicates that the system could not be shutdown within the time specified. The default timeout value is 5 minutes and the maximum value allowed is 1 hour.
SYS051.Resolution: Retry the operation with a longer specified graceful shutdown timeout or with the system shutdown option.
SYS051.Message: The system could not be shut down within the specified time.

SWC0300.Description: There is no coredump available to display.
SWC0300.Message: There is no coredump currently available.

PSU501.Description: The server was already up, when the user gave a power on request.

OSE1008.Description: The system OS has successfully booted from the CD-ROM.

CPU0819.Message: The power input for CPU %1 voltage regulator module has been restored.

UEFI0149.Message: The PERC storage adapter in %1 is not supported by the installed storage backplane.
UEFI0149.Resolution: Install a compatible storage adapter. For more information, see the platform Owner's Manual.
UEFI0149.Description: The PERC storage adapter identified in this message is not supported by the installed storage backplane.

JCP022.Message: Invalid Job ID %1 for scheduling or deletion operation.
JCP022.Resolution: Verify the job ID value by enumerating job instances and validating that the Job ID value is correct for the job being scheduled or deleted. Retry the operation with the correct Job ID value.
JCP022.Description: An invalid Job ID was provided as input for a scheduling or deletion operation. The Job ID indicated in the message does not match an existing Job on the target system.

SWU8514.Message: Unable to update the IOM infrastructure firmware of slot %1. ErrorCode=0x%2.
SWU8514.Resolution: Reacquire the Image file from the source folder, and then retry the operation.
SWU8514.Description: The IOM infrastructure firmware update operation is not successful.

UEFI0208.Message: An error occurred during DDR memory channel initialization on memory slots: %1.
UEFI0208.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Remove input power to the system, 2) Reseat the DIMM module and 3) Restart the system. If the issue persists, then replace the faulty memory module(s) identified in the message.
UEFI0208.Description: An error occurred during DDR memory initialization during the Command Clock Training - Group All phase.

LIC013.Description: The license includes features not supported in this firmware release.
LIC013.Resolution: Update the firmware to the latest version.
LIC013.Message: These license features are not supported by this firmware version.

PDR15.Description: This message is generated after a rebuild completes on a physical disk.

RAC1170.Description: Unable to find the SSL library. This can be because, the library is not installed in the default path or no SSL library is installed.
RAC1170.Resolution: If a SSL library is not installed, install one and retry the operation. If a SSL library is installed, create a soft-link of the installed SSL library to "libssl.so" using the linux "ln" command and retry the operation.
RAC1170.Message: Unable to find the SSL library in the default path.

VDR51.Message: The consistency check process made corrections and completed on %1.
VDR51.Description: The consistency check completed on the virtual disk after making corrections.

CTL76.Message: A configuration command could not be committed to disk on %1
CTL76.Resolution: Re-issue the failed configuration command or try with a different set of physical disks. Contact technical support if the problem persists.
CTL76.Description: The controller encountered errors while applying the configuration on the physical disks. The configuration command applied has not taken effect.

SWC0314.Description: The syntax of the getconfig command is invalid.
SWC0314.Resolution: Refer the help text for getconfig subcommand.
SWC0314.Message: Invalid syntax. The -o option requires -g to be specified also.

UEFI0118.Description: Card identification signature is not present on Internal Dual Secure Digital Module (IDSDM) SD card 2.
UEFI0118.Resolution: Do one of the following: 1) Check the IDSDM or the SD card media. 2) Try reseat or replace the SD card media. If the issue persists, contact your service provider.
UEFI0118.Message: Card identification signature is not present on Internal Dual Secure Digital Module (IDSDM) SD card 2.

VRM0013.Description: Simultaneously connecting Virtual Media and USB interface is not possible.
VRM0013.Resolution: Detach the USB interface and re-try.
VRM0013.Message: Virtual Media services is currently attached to the USB interface. It must be detached before the image server can be connected.

VLT0227.Message: The memory module %1 voltage is greater than the upper critical threshold.
VLT0227.Resolution: 1) Review system logs for power supply exceptions.2) Reseat the memory module.3) If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
VLT0227.Description: System hardware detected an over voltage or under voltage condition.If multiple voltage exceptions occur consecutively the system may power down in failsafe mode.

SUP0540.Description: The update packages cannot be installed because of insufficient space in the iDRAC even after deleting firmware installation files stored in the Rollback feature.
SUP0540.Resolution: Delete Lifecycle Controller related data by using the Repurpose or Retire System features, and then retry the operation.
SUP0540.Message: Unable to install update packages because of insufficient space in the iDRAC.

FC004.Resolution: Make sure that the input parameter values that are provided to the method match the parameter data type and possible values defined in the FC HBA Profile specification.
FC004.Description: The value for the specified parameter is invalid.

VFL0712.Resolution: Retry the task after a few minutes.
VFL0712.Message: One or more partitions are busy with another operation; the SD card could not be initialized.

SWU8523.Message: The firmware update operation of the iDRAC on the server in slot %1 is successfully completed.
SWU8523.Description: The firmware update operation of the iDRAC identified in the message is successful.

RAC1143.Message: Configuration results are not applicable for the job type for Job: %1.
RAC1143.Description: The job identified in the message is not a configuration job, a configuration XML import or preview type job that generates configuration results.

VFL0018.Description: The requested operation is currently in progress.
VFL0018.Resolution: Wait for the requested operation to complete.
VFL0018.Message: The requested operation is in progress.

SYS439.Description: The operation cannot be completed because the Secure Boot policy is set to Standard.
SYS439.Resolution: Reset the Secure Boot policy to Custom by performing the PATCH operation for the SecureBootPolicy attribute on the Redfish Bios URL.
SYS439.Message: Unable to complete the operation because the Secure Boot policy is set to Standard.

SUP0103.Description: The specified TFTP server is not reachable.
SUP0103.Resolution: Check if the TFTP server is alive.
SUP0103.Message: TFTP IP address is not reachable.

BIOS021.Description: The old BIOS password specified in the change BIOS password operation was incorrect.
BIOS021.Resolution: Retry the operation with correct old BIOS password.

DIS106.Description: The AutoConfig import file operation could not be successfully completed, because the shutdown type (-d) specified in the DHCP scope option field where the VendorID=iDRAC is incorrect.
DIS106.Resolution: Enter a valid shutdown type in the DHCP scope option field where the VendorID=iDRAC using (-d <0 or 1>) where 0 = Graceful shutdown and 1 = Forced shutdown.
DIS106.Message: Unable to start the AutoConfig file import operation, because an invalid shutdown type was specified in the DHCP scope option field where the VendorID=iDRAC.

SUP0506.Description: The catalog file in the selected repository is corrupt or compressed in an unsupported format.
SUP0506.Resolution: Select a repository with a valid catalog file, and retry the operation.
SUP0506.Message: Unable to decompress the catalog file.

SWC8519.Message: Successfully modified user name from %1 to %2.
SWC8519.Description: The user name identified in the message was successfully modified.

STOR072.Description: The configuration operation could not be performed because it requires iDRAC Service Module (ISM) service to be present and running in the server Operating System.
STOR072.Resolution: Make sure the iDRAC Service Module (ISM) service is running on the server Operating System and then retry the operation. Refer to the iDRAC User Guide for installing and starting ISM.
STOR072.Message: iDRAC Service Module (ISM) is either not present or not running on the server OS.

USR0017.Description: There are no active sessions on the iDRAC for the specified user.
USR0017.Message: No active sessions currently exist for the specified user.

SYS244.Message: Unable to transfer a file, %1, because of an unsupported proxy workgroup value.
SYS244.Resolution: Make sure that the correct proxy workgroup value is entered, and then retry the operation.
SYS244.Description: The file cannot be transferred because a proxy workgroup value is not entered, or the entered value is not supported.

PWR8666.Description: The iKVM power cycle operation is initiated.
PWR8666.Message: The iKVM power cycle operation is initiated.

HWC5002.Resolution: Check chassis fabric type in CMC GUI and compare to the type of IOM or mezzanine card.
HWC5002.Description: The fabric type for the IOM and mezzanine cards must match. Once an IOM or mezzanine card is inserted into the chassis, the fabric type is then set for the CMC and the CMC will ensure that all subsequent IOM's and mezzanine cards match.

USR0173.Description: The Front Panel USB port switched automatically from iDRAC to operating system.
USR0173.Message: The Front Panel USB port switched automatically from iDRAC to operating system.

LNK8501.Message: The network connection of server in slot %1 IOM in slot %2 port %3 is restarted.
LNK8501.Description: The network connection of the identified server to the external network is restored.

TMP0130.Description: Ambient air temperature is too cool.
TMP0130.Message: The control panel temperature is less than the lower warning threshold.

UEFI0198.Message: An error occurred during Scalable Memory Interconnect (SMI) initialization on memory riser %1.
UEFI0198.Resolution: Do the following: 1) Remove input power to the system, 2) Reseat the memory riser and 3) Restart the system. For more information, see the platform Owner's Manual.
UEFI0198.Description: An error occurred during Scalable Memory Interconnect initialization during the Read Level Fine Training phase.

PDR86.Message: Bad block table on %1 is full.
PDR86.Description: The number of blocks on the disk that exhibit an error has exceeded the capacity of the drive to remap. Any future writes to bad sectors will be unrecoverable.

PWR8671.Message: The Chassis Management Controller is unable to set the Enhanced Cooling Mode because the requested power %1 AC Watts exceeds the subsystem power limit %2 AC Watts for IO Modules, Blowers and Servers.
PWR8671.Resolution: Make sure the system operates within the subsystem Connector Limit for the components specified. To review power budget information select Chassis Overview -> Power -> Budget Status. Turn off unused components within the subsystem to make power available to set Enhanced Cooling Mode.
PWR8671.Description: The Enhanced Cooling Mode feature cannot be enabled because the requested power exceeds the Chassis subsystem power limit for IO Modules, Blowers and Servers.

RAC0609.Message: The job %1 has been successfully added to the job queue.
RAC0609.Resolution: No response action is required. The status of jobs can be viewed on the Job Queue page.
RAC0609.Description: The import or export system configuration operation with the job ID indicated in the message was successfully added to the Job Queue.

RAC1166.Message: Successfully initiated Configuration XML file preview operation that was invoked by %1.
RAC1166.Description: The Configuration XML file preview operation was successfully initiated after it was invoked by the user name identified in the message.

UEFI0170.Message: Unable to configure memory interleaving on DIMM modules on memory slots: %1.
UEFI0170.Resolution: Check the DIMM population and hardware configuration to make sure interleaving can be supported. For more information, see the platform Owner's Manual.
UEFI0170.Description: Memory could not be interleaved because of an attempt to simultaneously configure incompatible A7 mode and Target Address Decode (TAD) 3-way interleave during memory initialization.

VDR21.Description: This message is generated after a consistency check completes on a virtual disk.

NIC016.Message: AttributeValue cannot be changed for disabled AttributeName %1.
NIC016.Description: A set attribute operation was attempted on a disabled attribute.

PCI5007.Message: The auxiliary power-related issue of the PCIe adapter in slot %1 is resolved.
PCI5007.Description: The 3.3 Volt Regulator power related issue of PCIe carrier present in the slot identified in the message is resolved.

PWR8575.Message: Initiated the Virtual Reseat of server %1.
PWR8575.Description: A Virtual Reseat for the server identified in the message is initiated. A Virtual Reseat is the same as removing and inserting a server.

IOID110.Message: The virtual address of %1 Port %2 is configured.
IOID110.Description: The virtual address of NIC port identified in the message is configured.

SYS130.Description: Unable to create the final zip archive name because the Service Tag and time stamp could not be retrieved from OS interfaces.
SYS130.Resolution: Do the following: 1) On Windows, restart the WMI service and retry the operation, 2) Restart the OS and retry the operation.
SYS130.Message: OS Collector: Unable to create filename for zip archive.

VFL0019.Description: The requested vFlash media partition is already detached from the host operating system.
VFL0019.Message: The vFlash media partition is already in detached state.

SWC0057.Description: Unable to copy the file to the network share because it does not have the specified folder, the specified folder name has space between the characters, does not have enough free space, or is read-only.
SWC0057.Resolution: Make sure that the network share has the specified folder, the specified folder name has no space between the characters, has enough free space, or is not read-only. If the problem persists, perform an AC power cycle and retry the operation.
SWC0057.Message: Unable to export the file to the network share.

RAC0155.Description: While the system is powered off it is unable to retrieve information about system temperature.
RAC0155.Resolution: Turn the system on to view this information.
RAC0155.Message: Unable to retrieve the temperature information. The system is powered off.

ISM0023.Description: The feature WMI Information is disabled. It will be enabled when a compatible iDRAC firmware is installed.
ISM0023.Resolution: WMI Information feature requires iDRAC 8 firmware version 2.00.00 or later. Update the iDRAC firmware to the appropriate version to activate the WMI Information feature.
ISM0023.Message: The feature WMI Information is deactivated because the iDRAC firmware version installed is not compatible. It will be activated when the compatible iDRAC firmware is installed.

PCI1342.Message: A bus time-out was detected on a component at slot %1.
PCI1342.Resolution: Cycle input power, update component drivers, if device is removable, re-install the device.
PCI1342.Description: System performance may be degraded. The device has failed to respond to a transaction (master/target abort or completion timeout).

PWR1002.Description: To avoid shutdown, system performance has been degraded.
PWR1002.Resolution: Review system configuration and system logs for thermal or environmental failures and warnings.
PWR1002.Message: The system performance degraded because of thermal protection.

OSD54.Description: vFlash allows only 16 partitions to be created.
OSD54.Resolution: Make sure that there are less than 16 partitions before creating another partition on vFlash.

VDR101.Message: Virtual Adapter mapping reported for %1. Virtual Adapter 1 is now %2. Virtual Adapter 2 is now %3. Virtual Adapter 3 is now %4. Virtual Adapter 4 is now %5
VDR101.Description: Indicates the Virtual Disk to Virtual Adapter Mapping for audit purposes.

RAC1036.Description: Successfully cleared pending values for attributes in the group specified.
RAC1036.Resolution: To verify, run the RACADM command "racadm get group".
RAC1036.Message: Successfully cleared pending attribute(s) for the group specified.

PWR8562.Message: Unable to power on the server %1 before power on timer expired.
PWR8562.Resolution: The Server may need more time to power on. Wait for ten seconds and check the power status. If the server was not powered on, retry the operation. If the issue persists, remove and reinsert the server, wait for the iDRAC to complete startup, and retry the operation.
PWR8562.Description: Unable to power on the server before the power on timer has expired. This happens if the server did not show power on status change within 30 seconds after the power on operation was initiated. This issue may also occur when iDRAC is rebooting.

SYS002.Description: The operation did not complete successfully because of an unknown error in iDRAC.
SYS002.Resolution: Retry the action. If the issue persists, reset iDRAC.
SYS002.Message: Unable to perform the operation due to an unknown error in iDRAC.

PWR8598.Message: The Power Supply Unit (PSU) %1 is turned off because it is not compatible with the other PSUs used in the Chassis.
PWR8598.Resolution: Replace the PSU with an appropriate unit, and then retry the operation. For a list of PSUs that are compatible, consult the system Owner's Manual or contact your service provider.
PWR8598.Description: The Power Supply Unit (PSU) identified in the message is turned off because it is not compatible with the other PSUs in the Chassis.
