SWC8556.Description: The Boot Identity profile identified in the message is in use by the server that has the Service Tag identified in the message.

RAC0745.Description: There are no pending operations on the selected component group.
RAC0745.Message: There are no pending operations present on the selected component group.

RED025.Description: The firmware for the indicated device updated successfully to the identified firmware version.

USR0031.Message: Unable to log in for %1 from %2 using %3.
USR0031.Resolution: Make sure the login credentials are valid and retry the operation.
USR0031.Description: Unsuccessful login for the username, IP address, and interface identified in the message.

TMP0104.Message: The system board %1 temperature is outside of range.
TMP0104.Resolution: Check system operating environment and review event log for fan failures.
TMP0104.Description: Ambient air temperature is too warm or cool.

SUP014.Description: An unknown error was encountered while trying to delete the job.
SUP014.Resolution: Retry the action. If this fails, reboot the iDRAC.

RAC0668.Description: This setting will be applied during the next server restart. If the setting is not compatible with the RAID Controller, then LED status indicators on all the associated hard disk drives (HDDs) stop functioning.
RAC0668.Message: This setting will be applied during the next server restart. If the setting is not compatible with the RAID Controller, then LED status indicators on all the associated hard disk drives (HDDs) stop functioning.

VLT0224.Message: The memory module %1 voltage is less than the lower warning threshold.
VLT0224.Resolution: 1) Review system logs for power supply exceptions.2) Reseat the memory module.3) If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
VLT0224.Description: System hardware detected an over voltage or under voltage condition.If multiple voltage exceptions occur consecutively the system may power down in failsafe mode.

USR101.Description: Unable to allocate the resource because of the lack of memory or file space in the iDRAC firmware.
USR101.Resolution: Reset iDRAC and retry the operation.

SYS191.Description: The provided Server Configuration Profile is being applied to the system. The host may reboot to apply all changes.
SYS191.Resolution: No response action is required. Use the GetConfigResults() method to get the configuration job results or export the Lifecycle Log to review the configuration job results.

PSU0802.Message: The power supply redundancy policy on the system has been set to %1.
PSU0802.Description: The power supply redundancy policy on the system has been set.

BAR068.Description: The system profile export destination is not supported.
BAR068.Resolution: Insert, enable and initialize supported vFlash media and retry the operation.

PSU0078.Resolution: Review product documentation, change power supply with correct revision.
PSU0078.Description: This power supply revision is not supported for this system.

RAC058.Message: AttributeValue is not unique for AttributeName %1.
RAC058.Resolution: Provide a unique value for the specified attribute. For more information about the component being managed, see the DCIM Profile documentation.
RAC058.Description: The value provided for the specified attribute is not unique. For example, the user name for a user account must be unique.

SUP0118.Message: iDRAC reset failed. Please reset the iDRAC manually to complete the firmware rollback operation.

VDR44.Description: This alert is provided for informational purposes.

HWC5036.Message: A failure is detected on IO module %1.
HWC5036.Resolution: Contact technical support. Refer to your product documentation to choose the contact method that is convenient for you.
HWC5036.Description: The IOM module performance may be impact.

DIS016.Description: Provisioning Server responded to iDRAC IP address change.
DIS016.Message: Response received from Provisioning Server to the notification of iDRAC IP address change.

SWC0288.Message: Object %1 in %2 group must be specified. Line: %3
SWC0288.Resolution: Configure the object specified in the message in specified group, before performing a config to file action.
SWC0288.Description: The object specified in the message in the group specified in the message is not configured.

RAC1190.Description: Unable to configure the provisioning server.
RAC1190.Message: Unable to configure the Provisioning Server feature settings. The required options are either invalid or not provided.

RAC059.Description: When the Network Time Protocol (NTP) feature is enabled, the iDRAC will get time from the configured NTP server. Directly configuration of the iDRAC time is disabled when NTP is enabled.
RAC059.Resolution: Disable Network Time Protocol (NTP) and retry the operation.
RAC059.Message: Unable to configure iDRAC time because Network Time Protocol (NTP) is enabled.

PDR32.Resolution: Verify that the disk is healthy and installed. Check the cables. Refer to the product documentation and see the Cables Attached Correctly section for more information on checking the cables. If necessary, replace the disk and reassign the global hot spare.
PDR32.Description: The controller cannot to communicate with a disk that is assigned as a global hot spare. The disk either failed or was removed. There may also be a bad or loose cable.

STOR0110.Description: The specified Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDDs) system component name is invalid.
STOR0110.Resolution: Verify that the correct Fully Qualified Device Descriptor (FQDD) system component name is specified. See the help text (The help text for the raid subcommand can be obtained by running "racadm help raid") or documentation for valid FQDD system component names.

TMP8502.Description: The system has recovered from being unable to read planar board or control panel temperature sensors.
TMP8502.Message: Able to read planar board temperature sensors. Cooling set for normal chassis operation.

RRDU0007.Description: Internal Dual SD Module rebuild completed successfully.
RRDU0007.Message: Internal Dual SD Module rebuild completed successfully.

RAC016.Description: The method cannot be run because an invalid attribute name is entered.
RAC016.Resolution: Enter a valid attribute name and retry the operation.
RAC016.Message: Unable to run the method because an invalid attribute name is entered.

PDR81.Description: The physical disk firmware update operation has started.

RAC0294.Description: The amount of time iDRAC waits before sending a partial Serial Over LAN (SOL) data packet. This parameter is specified in milliseconds. It is recommended to use 10 milliseconds for optimal performance.
RAC0294.Resolution: Enter a valid Character Accumulate Interval value. Expected range: 1-255.
RAC0294.Message: The Character Accumulate Interval value is invalid. Expected range: 1-255.

SWC0242.Description: The license is missing or expired. This will result in the loss of functionality that is specific to the features supported by the license.
SWC0242.Resolution: Import an appropriate license to iDRAC. If you do not know which license to install, contact your service provider.
SWC0242.Message: A required license is missing or expired. Obtain an appropriate license and try again, or contact your service provider for additional details.

STOR0510.Description: Unable to apply the RAID controller encryption because RAID controller is not responding.
STOR0510.Resolution: Retry the operation. If the problem persists, reboot the system or update the RAID controller firmware to the latest version and retry the operation.

BAR051.Message: Performing Component Configuration Restore for Device : %1
BAR051.Description: The configuration import for the specified device is in progress.

RAC1176.Description: The Certificate Signing Request (CSR) message cannot be generated because all the attributes in the iDRAC.Security group are not configured.
RAC1176.Resolution: Make sure that all the attributes in the iDRAC.Security group are configured. To get the list of attributes, run the following command "racadm get iDRAC.Security".
RAC1176.Message: Unable to generate the Certificate Signing Request (CSR) message because all the attributes in the iDRAC.Security group are not configured.

BAR073.Description: The operation to delete the vFlash backup partition did not complete successfully.
BAR073.Resolution: Enable and initialize the vFlash media and retry the export. If the error continues, try a new vFlash media or use the network share option(s).
BAR073.Message: Delete of vFlash Backup partition unsuccessful.

PCI1322.Message: Bus performance degraded for a component at bus %1 device %2 function %3.
PCI1322.Resolution: Cycle input power, update component drivers, if device is removable, re-install the device.
PCI1322.Description: System performance may be degraded. The bus is not operating at maximum speed or width.

SWU8532.Message: Unable to update the LKVM firmware, because an invalid parameter is entered. ErrorCode=0x%1.
SWU8532.Description: The LKVM firmware update operation is not successful, because an invalid parameter is entered.

RAC0230.Description: This message is displayed when a confirmation is required to initialize the vFlash SD Card.
RAC0230.Resolution: Press OK to initialize the SD Card. This will erase all data. If undesired press Cancel.
RAC0230.Message: This operation erases all data in the SD Card. Do you want to continue?

SWC0254.Description: Local Configuration using RACADM may be disabled.
SWC0254.Resolution: Check if the Local Configuration using RACADM is disabled and enable it through GUI.
SWC0254.Message: Unable to perform requested operation. If the operation attempted was to configure DRAC, possible reason may be that Local Configuration using RACADM is disabled.

VF037.Description: The attaching partition operation did not complete successfully.
VF037.Message: Attach partition operation did not complete successfully.

LC062.Description: Export or Import server profile operation is already running. The operation may take a few minutes to compete.
LC062.Resolution: To retry the operation, wait for a few minutes.
LC062.Message: Export or Import server profile operation is already running.

LIC903.Resolution: To provide the correct parameters, see Lifecycle Controller-Remote Services documentation.
LIC903.Description: One or more parameters were not specified for the invoked method.

PDR93.Description: The physical disk firmware update operation has completed.

PCI3002.Message: Failed to program virtual MAC address on a component at bus %1 device %2 function %3.
PCI3002.Resolution: Update BIOS, BMC/iDRAC, LOM, and mezzanine card firmware. If problem persists please contact customer support.
PCI3002.Description: Either the BIOS, BMC/iDRAC, LOM, or NIC firmware is out of date and does not support FlexAddress.

SWC8607.Message: Quick Deploy Profile: Starting to apply profile %1 to server %2.
SWC8607.Description: The Quick Deploy of Profile process has started for the server identified in the message.

UEFI0109.Message: One or more memory errors have occurred on memory slot: %1.
UEFI0109.Resolution: Remove input power to the system, reseat the DIMM module and restart the system. If the issues persist, then replace the faulty memory module identified in the message.
UEFI0109.Description: One or more memory errors have occurred on memory slot identified in the message. The error occurred during write leveling initialization.

SUP021.Description: Diagnostics and USC updates are direct updates and cannot be scheduled.
SUP021.Resolution: Do not schedule USC or Diagnostics Jobs.
SUP021.Message: Diagnostics, Driver Pack or Lifecycle Controller update is a direct update and cannot be scheduled.

VF0060.Description: The SD card was not detected. Therefore, the requested operation cannot be completed.
VF0060.Resolution: Verify whether the SD card is inserted and enabled, then re-try.
VF0060.Message: Unable to perform the requested operation. Make sure the SD card is inserted and enabled.

TMP0107.Message: The memory module %1 temperature is less than the lower critical threshold.
TMP0107.Description: Ambient air temperature is too cool.

IOID006.Message: Storage Target Persistence Policy setting is changed to %1.
IOID006.Description: The Storage Target Persistence Policy setting is changed to the restart type identified in the message.

PST0013.Description: System extended memory test in progress.

VDR4.Description: This message is generated after a virtual disk was created on a controller.

SEL0014.Message: The System Event Log (SEL) was cleared by %1 from %2.
SEL0014.Description: The System Event Log (SEL) was cleared by the username identified in the message from the IP address identified in the message.

SEL1204.Description: The operating system or BIOS detected an unknown event. (IPMI sensor type code 12h - offset 02h).
SEL1204.Resolution: Reduce system to minimum supported configuration. If issues persists, contact support.
SEL1204.Message: An unknown system hardware failure detected.

PR16.Message: Some of the configuration values could not be applied to device: %1
PR16.Resolution: Check the current system configuration and ensure all settings are correct. If not, retry the operation.
PR16.Description: The device could not apply some of the configuration settings. This may indicate configuration changes since the last system inventory or mutually exclusive settings.

LOG006.Message: Test event generated for message ID %1.
LOG006.Description: This message is generated while performing a Test Event action. Performing a Test Event action logs an event in the Lifecycle Log with the user specified message ID. It may also generate events through SNMP, email, or other event notification sources if they are enabled. The test event does not indicate that there is a hardware or software problem. It provides a mechanism for users to test their event processing applications.

BAR094.Description: The request to create a System Profile Backup file did not complete successfully because there is already a request in progress.
BAR094.Resolution: If possible monitor the in progress job for completion and then retry the request. If that is not possible try clearing all jobs and try the request again. If the issue persists, restart the Integrated Remote Access Controller (iDRAC) and try the request again.
BAR094.Message: Another Backup operation already in progress.

RAC0601.Description: The server encountered an unexpected condition. This may be due to invalid JavaScript Object Notation.
RAC0601.Resolution: Wait for few minutes and refresh the page. If the problem persists, contact service provider.
RAC0601.Message: Unable to retrieve alert recurrence information.

VF020.Description: The number of partitions exceeded the maximum number allowed on a SD card.
VF020.Resolution: This SD card has reached the partition limit. Delete any partitions that are not necessary and try again.

RAC1034.Description: This operation will cause the server to shutdown immediately. This may result in the applications losing data.
RAC1034.Resolution: Before continuing, exit all the programs running on this server, and make sure that there is no inbound and outbound traffic associated with this server. Inability to do so may prevent all the servers in the chassis from accessing the shared-storage devices for up to two minutes. To continue the operation, enter a -f at the end of command "racadm serveraction powerdown -f", and then retry.
RAC1034.Message: This action will ungracefully turn off the server.

JCP036.Description: The job identified in the message is successfully deleted on iDRAC.

PWR1004.Description: To avoid shutdown, system performance has been degraded.
PWR1004.Resolution: If unintended, review system configuration changes and power policy.
PWR1004.Message: The system performance degraded because power capacity has changed.

RFLA2001.Message: Internal Dual SD Module %1 is absent.
RFLA2001.Resolution: If unintended, reinstall the SD module.
RFLA2001.Description: The SD card module is not detected or not installed.

SWC8505.Description: The description for the Profile identified in the message was edited.

RAC0641.Description: The job could not be successfully scheduled, because an invalid value is entered for 'time' while scheduling a job.
RAC0641.Resolution: Enter a correct value in the HH:MM format, and then retry the operation.
RAC0641.Message: Unable to schedule, because an invalid 'time' value is entered.

RED087.Description: Unable to update the Chassis firmware because the Allow CMC Updates Through OS and Lifecycle Controller setting is set to Disabled.
RED087.Resolution: Make sure that the Allow CHC Updates Through OS and Lifecycle Controller setting is set to Enabled, and then retry the operation. Using the iDRAC Web UI, select iDRAC > Update, click on the Settings tab, select Enabled for the setting and then click Apply button.
RED087.Message: Unable to update the Chassis firmware, Allow CMC Updates Through OS and Lifecycle Controller is set to Disabled.

OSD31.Description: Copying drivers for the selected operating system to network share failed. The share may be read-only or the Driver Pack present in Lifecycle Controller may be unusable.
OSD31.Resolution: 1) Make sure that the network share has write permission. 2) Update the Driver Pack using USC or DUP and then rerun the command.
OSD31.Message: Copying operating system drivers to network share failed

TMP0127.Description: Ambient air temperature is too warm or one or more fans may have failed.
TMP0127.Resolution: Check system operating environment and review event log for fan failures.
TMP0127.Message: Disk drive bay temperature is greater than the upper critical threshold.

SWC0219.Description: The syntax of the command is incorrect.
SWC0219.Resolution: Refer to the help for remote image command.
SWC0219.Message: The -p option requires -c to also be specified.

IOV005.Description: The Chassis Management Controller is not ready to run commands because the chassis must be turned on.
IOV005.Resolution: Turn on chassis and retry the command.
IOV005.Message: Chassis Management Controller (CMC) is not ready to run commands.

SWC0088.Description: The DHCP IP address of iDRAC cannot be retrieved because a network cable is not connected or a DHCP server is not functioning.
SWC0088.Resolution: Make sure that the network cable is connected, DHCP server is turned on, and then retry the operation. If the issue persists, perform the following steps: 1) Turn off the server and disconnect the power cord. 2) Wait for five seconds. 3) Reconnect the power cord, turn on the server, and then retry the operation.
SWC0088.Message: Unable to retrieve the iDRAC DHCP IP address.

RAC023.Description: Unable to enable the User or set values for IPMILan, IPMISerial, or User Admin Privilege because the User Password is not configured.
RAC023.Resolution: Set User Password before attempting to enable the other identified attributes.
RAC023.Message: Unable to enable the User or set values for IPMILan, IPMISerial, or User Admin Privilege because the User Password is not configured.

VLT0216.Message: The disk drive bay %1 voltage is outside of range.
VLT0216.Resolution: 1) Review system logs for power supply exceptions.2) Reseat hard disks in the bay. Reconnect all cables attached to the bay.3) If the problem persists, contact technical support. Refer to the product documentation to choose a convenient contact method.
VLT0216.Description: System hardware detected an over voltage or under voltage condition.If multiple voltage exceptions occur consecutively the system may power down in failsafe mode.

RAC0272.Description: If the Enable NIC checkbox is cleared, remote access to iDRAC is disabled.
RAC0272.Resolution: Disable NIC only if remote access is undesired.
RAC0272.Message: Disabling NIC will prevent the user from accessing the iDRAC remotely through Web GUI, Remote Racadm, Ssh, and Telnet. Local Racadm and serial interface will continue to work.

RAC0278.Description: This warning message appears when IPv6 is disabled.
RAC0278.Resolution: Use IPv4 network to access iDRAC remotely.
RAC0278.Message: Disabling IPv6 prevents access to iDRAC using an IPv6 address.

STOR097.Description: A virtual disk cannot be created because the memory size of the physical disk drive is less than available or entered virtual disk size.
STOR097.Resolution: Enter the FQDD of a physical disk drive that has a larger disk space, and then retry the operation. To view a list of physical disk drives and associated disk space, run the RACADM command "racadm storage get pdisks -o -p size". To view a list of virtual disks and associated size, run the RACADM command "racadm storage get vdisks -o -p size".
STOR097.Message: Unable to complete the operation because the memory size of the physical disk drive is less than the available or entered virtual disk size.

BAR071.Description: Access to the CIFS export/import destination is not possible or has been denied.
BAR071.Resolution: Verify that the input parameters are correct, connectivity exists to the destination end point, and retry the operation.

RAC0692.Description: Unable to assign and un-assign physical disk drives as global hotspare(s), because Lifecycle Controller is not enabled.
RAC0692.Resolution: To enable Lifecycle Controller, reboot the server. During server startup, press F2 to enter System Setup. Go to iDRAC Settings -> Lifecycle Controller, select Enable, and save the changes. Retry the operation after the server has restarted.
RAC0692.Message: Unable to assign and un-assign physical disk drives as global hotspare(s), because Lifecycle Controller is not enabled.

SWC1911.Message: User ID %1 User Password has been changed.
SWC1911.Description: User ID Password has been changed.

BAR097.Description: The current Lifecycle Controller Unified Server Configurator software installed on the system does not have Backup and Restore feature support.
BAR097.Resolution: Obtain the Lifecycle Controller Unified Server Configurator update package with Backup and Restore support, update the software and try the operation again.
BAR097.Message: Lifecycle Controller Unified Server Configurator incompatibility detected.

CTL75.Resolution: If data was corrupted or lost, restore the data to the disk from a backup copy.
CTL75.Description: The controller cache was discarded by the user. Data may have been lost or corrupted.

SWC0281.Description: The value being modified is READ only.
SWC0281.Message: The specified object is READ ONLY and cannot be modified.

VF047.Description: This is not a Dell-licensed VFlash.
VF047.Resolution: This feature requires a Dell SD card.

RAC1147.Description: The SNMPv3 user cannot be set because the user with the entered username for the SNMPv3 group is not present or enabled on iDRAC.
RAC1147.Resolution: Make sure the specified username is present on iDRAC and enabled, and retry the operation.
RAC1147.Message: Unable to set the SNMPv3 username entered in the command because the username is not present or enabled on iDRAC.

UEFI0074.Description: The system BIOS logs this message after detecting a change in Secure Boot policy settings. Such a change may result from user configuration or a system BIOS update. Changes to the following settings trigger this message: 1) Secure Boot (Enable/Disable) 2) Secure Boot Policy (Standard/Custom) 3) Platform Key 4) Key Exchange Keys 5) Authorized Signature Database (db) 6) Forbidden Signature Database (dbx).
UEFI0074.Resolution: Review the Secure Boot policy settings in System Setup > System BIOS > Security Settings page. If policy changes were expected, no action is necessary. Otherwise, modify the Secure Boot policy settings as needed.
UEFI0074.Message: The Secure Boot policy has been modified since the last time the system was started.

SWC0039.Description: The backup Server Configuration Profile image partition is not present in the vFlash SD card.
SWC0039.Resolution: A backup Server Configuration Profile is required to import or export a Server Profile. Perform the backup operation and retry import or export operation.
SWC0039.Message: Unable to find the backup Server Configuration Profile image.

CMC8577.Description: The Remote Access Controller (RAC) Kerberos Keytab is changed.
CMC8577.Message: The Remote Access Controller (RAC) Kerberos Keytab is changed.

CTL112.Message: The Loadbalance Mode of %1 is set to %2.
CTL112.Description: The Loadbalance Mode of the controller identified in the message is set to the value identified in the message.

JCP008.Description: Multiple attributes were set in the operation but some set attribute actions were not successful. For example, setting an attribute that is not valid for the component being configured.
JCP008.Resolution: Examine the results of the configuration job in the Lifecycle Log for the source of the errors. Modify the settings as necessary and resubmit the job.

RDU0002.Description: One of more fans have failed or have been removed or a configuration change occurred which requires additional fans.
RDU0002.Resolution: Remove and re-install failed fans or install additional fans.

SWC0265.Description: The option requested is not available on the DRAC being used.
SWC0265.Resolution: Refer to the help to get the list of commands/options valid for the DRAC.
SWC0265.Message: This option is not supported on this type of DRAC.
